      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI for NIH quantity of interest below 5% on production mesh; Richardson extrapolation applied across minimum three mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh study completed; GCI on fine mesh is 4.1% marginally meeting the 5% threshold, but medium mesh GCI of 12.4% indicates sensitivity to mesh density in impeller tip-clearance region. Achieved level 3 against required level 4 due to unresolved tip-clearance refinement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions fully replicate VAD operating envelope including hematocrit, temperature, and anticoagulation protocol; all boundary conditions traceable to clinical operating range.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump experiments were conducted at 37°C with bovine blood at 33% hematocrit. VAD clinical use spans 36–38°C with human blood at 25–45% hematocrit and anticoagulation variability. Temperature and hematocrit ranges partially overlap but anticoagulation effects on viscosity are not represented. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative agreement metric (e.g., E_rms) below 15% across all validation operating points with uncertainty intervals overlapping; systematic bias characterised.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error of 38% across 5 operating points with systematic under-prediction at high shear. Uncertainty intervals from Monte Carlo UQ campaign do not consistently overlap experimental measurements at high-flow conditions. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI (NIH) directly maps to regulatory decision QoI (absolute hemolysis index); no transformation or surrogate metric used.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct regulatory quantity of interest and is used without surrogate transformation. However, the power-law hemolysis model integrates a path-dependent Lagrangian exposure that introduces QoI sensitivity to particle-tracking resolution not fully characterised. Achieved level 3 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, flow regime, and operating conditions span the full VAD COU envelope; no extrapolation beyond validated parameter space.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry which differs from clinical VAD impeller geometry in blade count and tip-clearance ratio. Operating point coverage spans 3 of 5 target flow-speed combinations. Significant extrapolation required for remaining 2 operating points. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
