      "rationale": "Residual convergence to 1e-6 reported but iterative convergence error not formally separated from discretization error. No floating-point round-off analysis performed. Factor not assessed at required depth; flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing by qualified analyst not involved in original simulation; documented sign-off.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. Single analyst team executed all simulation and post-processing steps. Use error factor not assessed; flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty for power-law hemolysis constitutive relation quantified through comparison with alternative hemolysis models; epistemic uncertainty bound established.",
      "rationale": "Only the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model was employed. No comparison with alternative hemolysis constitutive models (e.g., Taskin, Arora) was performed. Model form uncertainty is the dominant unquantified source at MRL 5. Factor not assessed; flagged as critical epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All hemolysis model input parameters (C, alpha, beta coefficients; blood viscosity; inlet velocity profile) characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation completed with convergence demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ campaign (n=2000 LHS samples) propagated uncertainty in power-law coefficients C, alpha, beta and inlet velocity profile. Blood viscosity uncertainty modelled with fixed Newtonian assumption; non-Newtonian effects not included in uncertainty characterisation. Convergence of output variance demonstrated at n=1500. Achieved level 2 against required level 5 due to Newtonian assumption gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size sufficient for statistical characterisation of hemolysis variability; inter-laboratory reproducibility demonstrated across minimum two independent test facilities.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump experimental data sourced from single laboratory publication. No inter-laboratory reproducibility data available. Sample size (n=3 per operating point) insufficient for robust statistical characterisation of hemolysis variability. Factor not assessed; flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Computational model input parameters demonstrated equivalent to experimental test article parameters through dimensional analysis and parameter matching; any deviations quantified and their impact on QoI bounded.",
      "rationale": "No formal parameter equivalency analysis performed between CFD boundary conditions and experimental test article characterisation. Inlet turbulence intensity assumed 5% in CFD; not measured in experiment. Pump rotational speed tolerance (±2 RPM) impact on hemolysis not quantified. Factor not assessed; flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    }
